{"tag":"section","attrib":{"id":"idb9988b94-47c4-11f1-9a61-b1559996dfe8","identifier":"/us/usc/t18/s3285"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"3285"},"text":"§ 3285.","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" Criminal contempt","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"No proceeding for criminal contempt within ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t18/s402"},"text":"section 402 of this title","children":[],"tail":" shall be instituted against any person, corporation or association unless begun within one year from the date of the act complained of; nor shall any such proceeding be a bar to any criminal prosecution for the same act."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":null},{"tag":"sourceCredit","attrib":{"id":"idb9988b95-47c4-11f1-9a61-b1559996dfe8"},"text":"(","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/act/1948-06-25/ch645"},"text":"June 25, 1948, ch. 645","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/62/828"},"text":"62 Stat. 828","children":[],"tail":".)"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"notes","attrib":{"type":"uscNote","id":"idb9988b96-47c4-11f1-9a61-b1559996dfe8"},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"historicalAndRevision","id":"idb9988b97-47c4-11f1-9a61-b1559996dfe8"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Historical and Revision Notes","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Based on ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t28/s390"},"text":"section 390 of title 28","children":[],"tail":", U.S.C., 1940 ed., Judicial Code and Judiciary ("},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/act/1914-10-15/ch323/s25"},"text":"Oct. 15, 1914, ch. 323, § 25","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/38/740"},"text":"38 Stat. 740","children":[],"tail":")."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Word “criminal” was inserted before “contempt” in first line. Words “within ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t18/s402"},"text":"section 402 of this title","children":[],"tail":"” were inserted after “contempt”."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"The correct meaning and narrow application of title 28, U.S.C., 1940 ed., § 390, are preserved, as section 389 of that title is incorporated in sections 402 and 3691 of this title.","children":[],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Words “corporation or association” were inserted after “person”, thus embodying applicable definition of ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t28/s390a"},"text":"section 390a of title 28","children":[],"tail":", U.S.C., 1940 ed. (See reviser’s note under "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t18/s402"},"text":"section 402 of this title","children":[],"tail":".)"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":null}
